originalText.text: I want to to write this review to maybe this business will avoid making the same mistakes with the next person. I made a huge mistake of going to Dr Julia for Botox.  I waited 5 years to have it done because I don’t  like the unnatural look and the heavy eyebrow look and that’s what I asked her to not do and that I wanted to a natural look and she proceeded to tell me that she knew what she was doing and then told me she was giving me a mixed Botox, whatever that means.  The whole process was about the money and not what I wanted.  She then went on to give me a botched Botox.  I was willing to pay whatever she was asking me 300 for my frown lines and now I have from lines and heavy eyebrows because she didn’t spread out not only that I had a horrible headache for 3 days and whatever she used wasn’t Botox.  I then went on to see a different skilled dermatologist to try and fix it and he said that whatever she used wasn’t Botox. Spear yourself from this place if you can. There are many amazing skilled dermatologist in the city.  Whatever reviews she has must had been free service or friends and family because I’ll tell you she isn’t a skilled aesthetician and she doesn’t listen to her patient.

originalText.text: Juno Aesthetics has such a warm and welcoming ambiance. Right when I walked in, the ladies at the front desk were very kind. The esthetician was so professional and even gave me some helpful tips for taking care of my skin in between treatments. It's been three days since I received the HydraFacial and I'm still getting compliments on my glowing skin. It was such an amazing experience that I already have my next appointment booked!
